org.influxdata.platform

Interface WriteClient


  • public interface WriteClient
    Write time-series data into InfluxData Platform 2.0.

    The data are formatted in Line Protocol.

    Author:
    Jakub Bednar (bednar@github) (20/09/2018 10:58)

    • Method Detail

      • writeRecord

        void writeRecord(@Nonnull
                 String bucket,
                 @Nonnull
                 String organization,
                 @Nonnull
                 ChronoUnit precision,
                 @Nullable
                 String record)
        Write Line Protocol record into specified bucket.
        Parameters:
        bucket - specifies the destination bucket ID for writes
        organization - specifies the destination organization ID for writes
        precision - specifies the precision for the unix timestamps within the body line-protocol. Available values : ChronoUnit.NANOS, ChronoUnit.MICROS, ChronoUnit.MILLIS, ChronoUnit.SECONDS. Default value : TimeUnit.NANOSECONDS.
        record - specifies the record in InfluxDB Line Protocol. The record is considered as one batch unit.

        records - specifies the records in InfluxDB Line Protocol

      • listenEvents

        @Nonnull
<T extends AbstractWriteEvent> io.reactivex.Observable<T> listenEvents(@Nonnull
                                                                                Class<T> eventType)
        Listen the events produced by WriteClient.

        The WriteClient produces: WriteSuccessEvent, BackpressureEvent and WriteErrorEvent.

        Type Parameters:
        T - type of event to listen
        Parameters:
        eventType - type of event to listen
        Returns:
        lister for eventType events
